The research focuses on enhancing the ProCo loss function for contrastive learning in long-tailed recognition. Key areas for improvement include scalability, robustness to class imbalance, and theoretical foundations. Potential research directions include developing a more scalable version of the ProCo loss, improving its robustness, conducting deeper theoretical analysis, and applying it to new domains.

